   LSF_LOG_MASK=LOG_DEBUG LSB_DEBUG_NQS="LC_TRACE LC_EXEC" 
.sp 2
   Debugging is turned on when you define both parameters.
.sp 2
   To specify multiple log classes, use a space-separated list
   enclosed in quotation marks. For example:
.sp 2
   LSB_DEBUG_NQS="LC_TRACE LC_EXEC"
.sp 2
   This parameter can also be defined from the command line.
.sp 2 .SH "Valid values"
\fBValid values\fR
.sp 2
   For a list of valid log classes, see LSB_DEBUG_CMD.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   Not defined
.sp 2 .SH "See also"
\fBSee also\fR
.sp 2
   LSB_DEBUG_CMD, LSF_CMD_LOGDIR, LSF_CMD_LOG_MASK, LSF_LOG_MASK,
