.sp 2
   Defines how any two LSF_HPC_NCPU_* thresholds are combined.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   or
.sp 2
\fBLSF_HPC_NCPU_INCREMENT\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2 .SH "Syntax"
\fBSyntax\fR
.sp 2
   \fRLSF_HPC_NCPU_INCREMENT=\fR\fIincrement\fR
.sp 2 .SH "Description"
\fBDescription\fR
.sp 2
   Defines the upper limit for the number of CPUs that are
   changed since the last checking cycle.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   0
.sp 2
\fBLSF_HPC_NCPU_INCR_CYCLES\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2 .SH "Syntax"
\fBSyntax\fR
.sp 2
   \fRLSF_HPC_NCPU_INCR_CYCLES=\fR\fIincrement_cycles\fR
.sp 2 .SH "Description"
\fBDescription\fR
.sp 2
   Minimum number of consecutive cycles where the number of CPUs
   changed does not exceed LSF_HPC_NCPU_INCREMENT. LSF checks
   total usable CPUs every 2 minutes.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   1
.sp 2
\fBLSF_HPC_NCPU_THRESHOLD\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2 .SH "Syntax"
\fBSyntax\fR
.sp 2
   \fRLSF_HPC_NCPU_THRESHOLD=\fR\fIthreshold\fR
.sp 2 .SH "Description"
\fBDescription\fR
.sp 2
   The percentage of total usable CPUs in the LSF partition of a
   SLURM cluster.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   80
.sp 2
\fBLSF_HPC_PJL_LOADENV_TIMEOUT\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2 .SH "Syntax"
\fBSyntax\fR
.sp 2
   \fRLSF_HPC_PJL_LOADENV_TIMEOUT=\fR\fItime_seconds\fR
.sp 2 .SH "Description"
\fBDescription\fR
.sp 2
   Timeout value in seconds for PJL to load or unload the
   environment. For example, set LSF_HPC_PJL_LOADENV_TIMEOUT to
   the number of seconds needed for IBM POE to load or unload
   adapter windows.
.sp 2
   At job startup, the PJL times out if the first task fails to
   register with PAM within the specified timeout value. At job
   shutdown, the PJL times out if it fails to exit after the last
   Taskstarter termination report within the specified timeout
   value.
.sp 2 .SH "Default"
\fBDefault\fR
.sp 2
   LSF_HPC_PJL_LOADENV_TIMEOUT=300
.sp 2
\fBLSF_ID_PORT \fR
